You are helping build NammaGear, a peer-to-peer marketplace for Bangalore students to buy and sell used electronics (laptops, monitors, keyboards, etc.).

## Stack
- Monorepo with pnpm workspaces: apps/web (Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind, shadcn/ui) and apps/api (Express, TypeScript, Prisma, PostgreSQL).
- Auth: JWT in httpOnly cookies (cookie name: ng_token). Never put tokens in localStorage.
- Images: Cloudinary (never local disk).
- Validation: Zod on every API endpoint, both body and params.
- Database: PostgreSQL via Prisma. All queries go through the Prisma client in apps/api/src/db.ts.

## Conventions
- All API routes under /api prefix.
- Use async/await, never callbacks. Wrap async route handlers to forward errors to the error middleware.
- Every new API endpoint: define a Zod schema first, then validate req.body with it.
- Prisma models are the source of truth for types; import types from @prisma/client, don't redefine.
- Frontend: use TanStack Query for all server state. No useEffect fetching.
- Frontend: use shadcn/ui components. Don't build form inputs from scratch.
- Pincode validation: use isBangalorePincode() from apps/api/src/lib/bangalore.ts on every listing create/update.
- Error responses: { error: string, details?: any } with appropriate HTTP status.
- Never log passwords, tokens, or full user records.

## Rules
- No any types. Use unknown and narrow, or define proper types.
- No direct process.env access in business logic — read env at the entry point and pass config down.
- Every database write that touches 2+ tables must be a Prisma transaction.
- Keep route handlers thin. Business logic in /services, data access in /db.
- Do not add new dependencies without telling me first.

## Product rules (hard constraints)
- Only Bangalore pincodes (560001-560103) are allowed for listings.
- Only authenticated users can create listings.
- Users can only edit/delete their own listings (enforce in the service layer).
- Listings have conditions: A (like new), B (good), C (fair).
- Listings have status: ACTIVE, SOLD, REMOVED.
- Max 5 images per listing.
- Contact happens via WhatsApp deep link — the API returns the seller's phone number only when authenticated.

## When I ask for a feature, output in this order:
1. The Prisma schema changes (if any), as a migration description
2. The Zod schema
3. The service function
4. The route handler
5. The frontend hook (TanStack Query)
6. The UI component
Do not skip steps. Do not output pseudocode.
